  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious criminal offense with significant legal consequences. If caught, potential penalties may include:\n\n1. Criminal Charges\n- Federal or state criminal prosecution\n- Potential felony charges\n- Prison sentences (typically 5-20 years)\n- Large monetary fines\n\n2. Financial Penalties\n- Substantial monetary sanctions\n- Asset seizure\n- Forfeitures of illegally obtained funds\n\n3. Additional Consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Professional license revocation\n- Difficulty obtaining future employment\n- Potential deportation for non-citizens\n\n4. Civil Penalties\n- Potential civil lawsuits\n- Additional financial penalties\n- Potential restitution requirements\n\nThe specific consequences depend on factors like:\n- Amount of money laundered\n- Specific methods used\n- Prior criminal history\n- Jurisdiction\n- Specific circumstances of the case\n\nProsecution typically involves investigations by agencies like the FBI, IRS, and federal prosecutors.",
